| Canvas section        | What to include                                                                     | Quality expectation                                                      |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Game title            | Final or working name of the game.                                                  | Clear, memorable and suitable for the target audience                    |
| Target audience       | Exact user group, age and context.                                                  | Not just "children" - be specific, e.g., 10-year-old children            |
| Cyber-safety topic    | The online safety issue being taught.                                               | Phishing, passwords, online privacy, cyberbullying, scams or safe gaming |
| Learning objective    | What the player should learn by playing.                                            | Measurable and linked to cyber safety                                    |
| Game format           | Web game, quiz, card game, board game, app mock-up, Twine story, Scratch game, etc. | Realistic for the team and time available                                |
| Core gameplay loop    | What the player repeatedly does.                                                    | Example: read challenge → choose answer → receive feedback → earn reward |
| UX design choices     | Colours, layout, buttons, background, icons and characters.                         | Clearly justified based on target audience                               |
| Accessibility choices | Large text, simple words, contrast, icons, clear feedback, inclusive visuals.       | Specific choices, not vague statements                                   |
| Reward and motivation | Stars, badges, points, level progress or positive messages.                         | Explains how the game keeps the user engaged                             |
| Success measure       | How the group will know the user learned something.                                 | Example: answer 5 questions and explain 3 safety rules                   |
